<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 08 at 8:43PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...Snow at Higher Elevations This Evening...
Temperatures have cooled into the lower 30s to lower 40s across
the mountains this evening, with readings into the mid 20s above
4000 feet. Rain showers have changed to snow snowers, especially
at higher elevations.
Light snow accumulations are expected tonight. Most locations will
have less than one half inch. Areas on west facing slopes will get
around one inch, with favored locations like Mt. Rogers, Beech
Mountain and western Greenbrier County picking up close to two
inches.
Use caution when driving through the mountains tonight. The road
may be slick in spots along the Blue Ridge Parkway south of
Roanoke and at other locations above 3000 feet.</description>
